Author: davidw
Title: History of Slashdot
Content:
Perhaps it's not as exciting, shiny or new as digg or reddit, but the recent stories on the history of Slashdot have been fairly interesting. It's worth noting that they were about as far from an SV startup as you can get.

Part 1: http://meta.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/10/02/1553218

Part 2: http://meta.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/10/10/1445216

Part 3: http://meta.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/10/17/1412245

Their setup, part 1, hardware: http://meta.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/10/18/1641203\n

Author: andreyf
Content: I'm surprised we don't see this in other places. Why doesn't Craigslist have a completely open API? Why not ebay? Is there really no market for a completely open auctioning community?
